==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Here
<hw>Here</hw> <pr>(h⟦emac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>her</ets>, AS. <ets>h⟦emac⟧r</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>h⟦emac⟧r</ets>, D. <ets>hier</ets>, OHG. <ets>hiar</ets>, G.
<ets>hier</ets>, Icel. & Goth. <ets>h⟦emac⟧r</ets>, Dan. <ets>her</ets>,
Sw. <ets>h⟦aum⟧r</ets>; fr. root of E. <ets>he</ets>. See
<er>He</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In this place; in the place where
the speaker is; -- opposed to <ant>there</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is not <qex>here</qex>, for he is risen.</q> <rj><qau>Matt.
xxviii. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the present life or state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Happy <qex>here</qex>, and more happy hereafter.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To or into this place; hither.
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> See <er>Thither</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Here</qex> comes Virgil.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou led'st me <qex>here</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>At this point of time, or of an argument;
now.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The prisoner <qex>here</qex> made violent efforts to rise.</q>
<rj><qau>Warren.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Here</xex>, in the last sense, is sometimes used
before a verb without subject; as, <xex>Here goes</xex>, for Now
(something or somebody) goes; -- especially occurring thus in drinking
healths. ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Here's</xex> [a health] to thee,
Dick.⟦rdquo⟧</note> <rj><au>Cowley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Here and there</b></col>, <cd>in one place and another;
in a dispersed manner; irregularly.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Footsteps <xex>here and
there</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Longfellow.</au> -- <col><b>It is neither, here
nor there</b></col>, <cd>it is neither in this place nor in that,
neither in one place nor in another; hence, it is to no purpose,
irrelevant, nonsense.</cd><-- mostly used to mean "irrelevant" -->
<au>Shak.</au></cs></p>

<p><ent>Hereabouts</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Herea-bout</ent>⟦br⟧
